A Bloemfontein resident was held at knifepoint &#038; thrown off a bridge in Canelands &#8211; Verulam by three suspects on Friday night.Reaction Unit South Africa reported that the man&#8217;s colleagues brought the heavily injured man to their base for medical attention around 20h00.It is alleged that the man was walking across the bridge when three African male suspects surrounded him.At knife point they demanded his belongings but a passing car disturbed them. They pushed the man off the bridge and fled.The man suffered bodily injuries after he fell on a huge rock when he was thrown off the bridge. The suspect fled without taking any items.The victim could not provide further descriptive details.